# Cloudflare Pages headers. https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# IMPORTANT: Pages ignores Cache-Control set here for static assets — it forces
# `max-age=14400` (4h) on JS/CSS and `max-age=0` on HTML, regardless of this
# file. That 4h JS cache desyncs with fresh HTML after a deploy (old cached
# app.js vs new index.html), which can crash a tool on load.
#
# The fix lives at the ZONE level (bantay.co), not here — a Transform Rule
# (Modify Response Header) for host `tools.bantay.co` that sets:
#   Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
# ETags make that cheap (304s) and keep JS in lockstep with HTML.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
